cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper proposes to use language referring expressions to identify target objects in videos. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper leverages recent advances in language grounding models designed for images to extend them to video data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper proposes an alternative way of identifying target objects using language specifications. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as the paper deals with video data and proposes a method for video object segmentation.
